In total, we identified seven papers addressing incident cases of psychosis linked to a virus. This included four observational studies (
 Kim et al., 2018; 
 Lee et al., 2004; 
 Mak et al., 2009; 
 Sheng et al., 2005), of which three were associated with exposure to SARS (
 Lee et al., 2004; 
 Mak et al., 2009; 
 Sheng et al., 2005), and one MERS (
 Kim et al., 2018). Additionally, we identified two case reports of patients with the H1N1 (
 Chang et al., 2015) and SARS (
 Cheng et al., 2004) and one study examined coronavirus immunoreactivity in people with recent-onset psychosis (
 Severance et al., 2011). All of the studies included in the review indicated a link between exposure to the virus and psychosis.
